WEBVTT

00:39.958 --> 00:41.960
<font color="#D900D9">(BIRDS CHIRPING)</font>

00:55.473 --> 00:57.475
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH PANTING)</font>

01:24.627 --> 01:26.129
I love you, Billy.

01:42.186 --> 01:43.187
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL SCREAM)</font>

01:43.354 --> 01:44.355
Oh, my God.

01:45.148 --> 01:47.108
<font color="#D900D9">(CRUZ SHRIEKING)</font>

01:47.275 --> 01:48.651
<font color="#D900D9">(LITA & JULIAN CHUCKLING)</font>

01:49.861 --> 01:52.196
Damn it, Billy. I think you broke my jaw.

01:52.697 --> 01:55.199
You fucking deserve it,
you assholes!

01:55.366 --> 01:56.826
Oh, are you okay, baby?
No.

01:56.993 --> 01:58.703
Get the fuck out of here!

01:58.870 --> 02:00.997
What the hell are you doing
dressed like that?

02:01.164 --> 02:03.666
For the Mountain Man Festival,
thought we'd dress up.

02:03.833 --> 02:05.668
Yeah, where are your costumes?

02:05.835 --> 02:07.211
What?
We don't have any.

02:07.378 --> 02:10.298
You can't go without a costume.
It shows lack of commitment.

02:10.465 --> 02:13.384
Can we have this conversation
after I can get dressed?

02:13.551 --> 02:15.470
Okay. Okay.

02:16.012 --> 02:17.263
Nice, Billy. Ha-ha-ha.
Grrr...

02:17.430 --> 02:20.350
Nice. Assholes.

02:22.852 --> 02:26.147
<font color="#808080">KALEEN:</font> This is Kaleen Webber, reporting
from the small town of Fairlake...

02:26.314 --> 02:29.067
...which, once a year,
turns into a big town on Halloween...

02:29.233 --> 02:32.236
...due to the 10th annual
Mountain Man Music Festival.

02:32.403 --> 02:35.031
People from all over the country
descend upon Fairlake...

02:35.198 --> 02:39.577
...for a weekend of music, partying and fun
at the fairgrounds just outside town.

02:39.744 --> 02:42.622
The festival has grown over the years
to where it now rivals...

02:42.789 --> 02:44.707
...Coachella and Lollapalooza.

02:44.874 --> 02:48.795
But some say that its free spirit and rowdy
crowds reminds them of Burning Man...

02:48.961 --> 02:51.422
...which has local officials concerned
on this night.

02:51.881 --> 02:54.425
Now back to you at the studio.

02:54.592 --> 02:56.135
Great.<font color="#808080">
KALEEN:</font> Here's the deal.

02:56.302 --> 02:58.930
I'm going for a run
to get my head out of this town crap.

02:59.097 --> 03:01.349
I'll meet you here for the live feed at 11.

03:01.516 --> 03:03.601
And everything better be ready to go.

03:04.227 --> 03:05.603
Go away, kid.
Ha-ha-ha.

03:15.196 --> 03:17.907
Hurry up. We gotta get on the road.
I don't wanna be late.

03:18.074 --> 03:20.118
All right,
give me a minute to get up first.

03:20.284 --> 03:23.079
We heard you're the one-minute man.

03:23.246 --> 03:24.288
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISTLES)</font>

03:24.455 --> 03:26.791
No. I assure you he has no problems
in that department.

03:26.958 --> 03:29.919
All right. I'm starving.
I gotta make breakfast first.

03:30.086 --> 03:33.881
Aw, come on, Billy.<font color="#808080">
BILLY:</font> You gotta start your day out right.

03:35.091 --> 03:38.094
<font color="#D900D9">(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

03:47.353 --> 03:48.730
<font color="#D900D9">(ROCK MUSIC
PLAYING OVER HEADPHONES)</font>

03:49.105 --> 03:50.982
Ha, ha.

03:53.651 --> 03:54.652
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

03:55.111 --> 03:57.238
Nice costume, creep.

04:02.994 --> 04:04.704
<font color="#D900D9">(CACKLING)</font>

04:04.871 --> 04:06.956
You know what? I'm sick of this.

04:07.498 --> 04:11.586
I'm sick of you kids partying,
making a mess and trying to scare people.

04:11.753 --> 04:13.880
Well, you know what?
You don't scare me.

04:14.046 --> 04:16.923
So fuck you. Go home.

04:18.176 --> 04:20.178
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

04:21.596 --> 04:23.347
<font color="#D900D9">(CACKLES)</font>

04:23.514 --> 04:26.809
<font color="#808080">KALEEN:</font> Help me! Help me, please!
Somebody help me!

04:26.976 --> 04:29.562
Hey, hey. Over here.

04:29.729 --> 04:33.065
Oh, please help. They're chasing me.

04:33.232 --> 04:34.358
Follow me. This way.

04:34.525 --> 04:36.527
<font color="#D900D9">(SOBBING)</font>

04:39.781 --> 04:41.407
Down here.

04:52.210 --> 04:53.544
<font color="#D900D9">(WHIMPERING)</font>

05:06.390 --> 05:07.475
Okay.

05:08.351 --> 05:09.852
Okay, I think they've gone.

05:10.561 --> 05:13.397
Thank you.
You saved me from those maniacs.

05:13.564 --> 05:16.234
Hey, you're bleeding pretty badly there.

05:16.400 --> 05:17.944
Let me fix that for you.

05:18.110 --> 05:19.904
Thank God for you.

05:20.071 --> 05:21.197
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

05:21.364 --> 05:25.076
Yeah. Thank God for me.

05:25.618 --> 05:28.246
Now, you keep pressure on that.
Mm-hm.

05:28.412 --> 05:30.248
You stay here.
Okay.

05:30.414 --> 05:32.500
I'm gonna make sure they've gone.

05:37.296 --> 05:43.427
Okay, it's all clear. This way.
Okay. Okay, okay, okay.

05:45.721 --> 05:46.931
But there's, uh...

05:47.098 --> 05:50.059
There's just one thing I forgot.
What?

05:51.060 --> 05:52.436
This.

05:52.603 --> 05:53.771
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

06:01.362 --> 06:03.072
<font color="#D900D9">(KALEEN SCREAMS THEN GRUNTING)</font>

06:18.629 --> 06:22.091
Hey, give me a hand, will you?

06:26.804 --> 06:28.139
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

06:30.725 --> 06:32.560
No, you fucking idiot.

06:33.269 --> 06:35.354
The body.

06:38.649 --> 06:40.902
Jesus fucking Christ.

06:41.193 --> 06:43.195
(PLAYING DOWN-TEMPO MUSIO

07:04.884 --> 07:07.595
Wake and bake, brother.
Thanks.

07:08.804 --> 07:10.848
Heh. You're such a slob.

07:11.015 --> 07:13.643
Can you try
and be a little bit cleaner for me?

07:13.809 --> 07:14.936
What?
You look like a pig.

07:15.102 --> 07:16.103
<font color="#D900D9">(SNORTS)</font>

07:16.270 --> 07:17.271
All right. Check it out.

07:17.438 --> 07:20.441
I got all our party favors arranged
by date and time.

07:21.025 --> 07:23.027
So this is cutting into my overhead.

07:23.194 --> 07:28.032
But in honor of this weekend and Julian's
great idea for us to come out here...

07:28.199 --> 07:29.825
...I've made an exception.

07:29.992 --> 07:33.371
First up, some chronic,
which you're participating in.

07:33.537 --> 07:38.209
And then some X
for when we go trick or treating...

07:38.376 --> 07:41.045
...and some shrooms
for when the bands start playing. Oh.

07:41.796 --> 07:43.965
You've been out of school
for two semesters.

07:44.131 --> 07:47.218
What do your parents think?
Oh, no. They don't know shit.

07:47.385 --> 07:49.720
And I wanna keep it that way.

07:49.887 --> 07:53.891
Ah, besides, you know,
I'm a budding entrepreneur.

07:54.058 --> 07:56.394
Why did we have to come
all the way out here?

07:56.560 --> 08:00.898
Because it's Mountain Man, baby.

08:01.065 --> 08:03.567
Hey, come on, look,
we could have gone to Burning Man.

08:03.734 --> 08:06.654
But I'm not gonna drive
all the way across country.

08:06.821 --> 08:08.614
We got a homegrown version of it here.

08:08.781 --> 08:12.410
Yeah. Mountain Man has got a much
more interesting story to it, anyway.

08:13.244 --> 08:16.247
You know the story, Cruz?
I'm not from around here, remember?

08:16.414 --> 08:19.250
Okay, well, we're going
to a small town called Fairlake.

08:19.417 --> 08:22.169
It was founded in 1814
or some shit like that.

08:22.336 --> 08:26.674
Well, apparently, the local miners didn't
get along too well with the hill people.

08:26.841 --> 08:28.759
I guess it was a territory dispute.

08:28.926 --> 08:31.220
There was conflicts
over the next couple of years.

08:31.387 --> 08:36.600
Now, Halloween night, 1817...

08:36.767 --> 08:39.145
...the entire town
was ravaged by hillbillies...

08:39.311 --> 08:42.690
...in the largest massacre
in the state's history.

08:42.940 --> 08:44.942
The only problem
was no bodies were found.

08:45.109 --> 08:48.112
It was just... Just blood. Lots of it.
It was... You know, it...

08:48.279 --> 08:52.366
The entire town,
every inhabitant disappeared.

08:52.867 --> 08:54.994
Was never seen again.

08:56.120 --> 08:58.706
<font color="#808080">CRUZ:</font> That's awful.
Well...

08:59.373 --> 09:03.127
Legend has it, the hillbillies hauled
all the bodies up to the woods...

09:03.294 --> 09:08.632
...created a huge bonfire and then
they cooked the fair residents of Fairlake.

09:10.718 --> 09:12.928
Well... And then they ate them.

09:15.598 --> 09:16.849
Bah!

09:17.016 --> 09:19.435
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGH)</font>

09:19.602 --> 09:23.981
Okay, you know what? I don't wanna go.
Oh, come on, baby, we're almost there.

09:24.148 --> 09:27.318
No. I don't wanna celebrate a massacre.

09:27.485 --> 09:29.070
It's innocent fun.
It's wrong.

09:29.236 --> 09:32.239
We'll just go tonight, we'll leave
tomorrow, okay? Come on, Cruz.

09:32.406 --> 09:33.991
Just one night, huh?

09:34.158 --> 09:35.826
Please?

09:35.993 --> 09:38.913
(PLAYING DOWN-TEMPO MUSIO

09:39.080 --> 09:40.664
Okay, fine.

09:40.831 --> 09:42.833
It is fine.

09:43.334 --> 09:44.668
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

09:45.377 --> 09:47.379
<font color="#D900D9">(CLANKING)</font>

10:10.736 --> 10:12.029
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

10:38.389 --> 10:41.517
What the fuck is all this shit?

10:41.684 --> 10:44.353
What have I told you about this?

10:45.354 --> 10:48.732
I told you a thousand fucking times...

10:48.899 --> 10:54.113
...you never leave anything behind.

10:54.280 --> 11:00.244
You never ever leave anything behind!

11:00.786 --> 11:03.747
What if somebody found this, huh?

11:03.914 --> 11:08.335
Then you got oops investigating,
snooping around.

11:08.502 --> 11:12.673
You don't live in some goddamn hospital
in the middle of nowhere any more.

11:12.840 --> 11:17.428
You live closer to civilization,
a lot fucking closer!

11:18.095 --> 11:22.099
I have been doing this for 30 years...

11:22.391 --> 11:25.102
...and I have never had to move.

11:25.769 --> 11:28.063
Do you know why?

11:28.230 --> 11:33.068
Because I never leave shit behind!

11:33.569 --> 11:37.573
I swear to fucking God,
you three pinheads...

11:37.781 --> 11:41.368
...you'd all be under lock and key by now
if I hadn't have happened across you.

11:41.619 --> 11:42.870
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLS THEN GRUNTING)</font>

11:45.956 --> 11:52.129
You live in my fucking house now
and you play by my fucking rules.

11:52.296 --> 11:54.798
You do as I say...

11:55.216 --> 11:59.970
...or I swear to God,
I will take you all down, kin or no kin.

12:02.640 --> 12:04.642
Get her processed.

12:14.151 --> 12:16.320
Looking forward to the trip?
Yeah.

12:16.487 --> 12:19.865
Thinking about getting me
a new .30-60 for the occasion.

12:20.032 --> 12:22.493
It was lucky of Jason
to win the bear license lottery.

12:22.660 --> 12:24.495
I know. He's very excited.

12:24.662 --> 12:28.499
Well, he's a good guy to invite me along.
I know. That's why I married him.

12:28.666 --> 12:31.835
You sure you don't wanna come?
I've got a job to do.

12:32.002 --> 12:33.796
You need to learn to relax a bit.

12:33.963 --> 12:37.758
You're always so by-the-book.
You ride us like we're in the military.

12:37.925 --> 12:40.427
Discipline, Junior,
it's a good tool to use in life.

12:46.016 --> 12:47.685
<font color="#808080">BIGGS:</font>
Ready for tonight?

12:47.851 --> 12:51.689
Mob of kids, such a pain in the keester.

12:51.855 --> 12:53.816
It should be a big night
for drunk and disorderly.

12:53.983 --> 12:56.568
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGS)</font>

12:57.194 --> 12:58.195
Sheriff Carter.

12:58.362 --> 13:01.407
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> <i> Who is the sexiest sheriff
in all of Greenbrier County?</i>

13:01.573 --> 13:04.118
I'm the only sheriff in Greenbrier County.

13:04.285 --> 13:05.911
Still doesn't mean you're not sexy.

13:06.078 --> 13:08.706
Hey, I just blew off the second shift.
I'm headed home.

13:08.872 --> 13:10.666
That's good.

13:11.166 --> 13:13.877
Junior's buying a new rifle
for your hunt this weekend.

13:14.044 --> 13:15.421
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

13:15.587 --> 13:17.506
Tell him it won't make him a better shot.

13:18.007 --> 13:19.174
Yeah, I already did.

13:19.341 --> 13:21.468
<i>I'm gonna fix some lasagna tonight
for dinner.</i>

13:21.635 --> 13:25.055
I'll stop by and bring you some?
That would be great.

13:25.222 --> 13:27.224
But call first. It's gonna be a busy night.

13:27.391 --> 13:29.310
<i>I may head down to the fairgrounds.</i>

13:29.476 --> 13:31.145
Then I'll bring it to you there.

13:31.312 --> 13:32.896
I'll call you later. Bye, honey.

13:33.063 --> 13:35.024
Okay, bye, honey.

13:38.610 --> 13:41.697
<font color="#D900D9">(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)</font>

13:41.864 --> 13:43.866
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

13:45.409 --> 13:46.577
<font color="#808080">GUS:</font>
Gotta turn this up.

13:46.744 --> 13:48.871
There's supposed to be
about 20 bands there.

13:49.038 --> 13:51.582
Oh, who's playing?
The Cheetah Whores.

13:51.749 --> 13:53.000
Oh, who are they?

13:53.167 --> 13:55.502
An all-girl band. Freaking awesome.
Yeah.

13:55.669 --> 13:56.962
Gus' favorite band.<font color="#808080">
CRUZ:</font> Oh.

13:57.129 --> 13:59.506
If they're so awesome,
why haven't I heard of them?

13:59.673 --> 14:01.925
You're from the West Coast.
They don't play there.

14:02.092 --> 14:04.261
When are you gonna go back, by the way?
Mm, June.

14:04.428 --> 14:06.263
But just for a month to see my parents.

14:06.430 --> 14:08.474
Billy is coming with me.
Yeah.

14:08.640 --> 14:11.810
<font color="#808080">LITA:</font> Nice.
We are gonna have an epic time.

14:11.977 --> 14:14.271
Meeting the folks?
That's getting pretty serious.

14:14.438 --> 14:17.775
Who? Me? Serious? Never.

14:17.941 --> 14:19.777
Look out!

14:20.611 --> 14:23.072
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL SCREAMING)</font>

14:34.333 --> 14:35.626
Is everyone okay?

14:35.793 --> 14:37.461
Is anybody hurt?

14:37.628 --> 14:40.631
I'm all right.<font color="#808080">
CRUZ:</font> No, we're okay.

14:46.053 --> 14:48.263
Oh, shit.

14:48.430 --> 14:49.473
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHING)</font>

14:49.640 --> 14:51.809
Where did he come from?

14:52.309 --> 14:53.310
Did We hit him?

14:54.144 --> 14:55.646
<font color="#808080">BILLY:</font>
I'm not sure.

14:56.146 --> 14:57.815
Well, we should see if he's dead.

15:02.236 --> 15:04.613
You guys, stay here.

15:07.074 --> 15:08.158
Goddamn it.

15:08.325 --> 15:10.494
I didn't see him in the rain.

15:18.293 --> 15:21.630
Yeah, I think he's dead.
But I didn't hit him.

15:24.216 --> 15:25.342
You must have.

15:26.051 --> 15:27.177
<font color="#808080">BILLY:</font>
Hey.

15:27.344 --> 15:28.637
<font color="#D900D9">(BILLY GROANS)</font>

15:28.804 --> 15:30.180
Fuck you!
Unn!

15:30.848 --> 15:32.349
<font color="#808080">GUS:</font>
You trying to fuck with us?

15:32.516 --> 15:34.768
<font color="#808080">BILLY:</font> Get up.<font color="#808080">
GUS:</font> You piece of shit.

15:35.352 --> 15:37.104
<font color="#D900D9">(MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

15:39.648 --> 15:41.483
<font color="#D900D9">(SIREN WAILING)</font>

15:45.154 --> 15:47.781
Freeze.
Put your hands on your head.

15:47.948 --> 15:50.200
<font color="#808080">BILLY:</font> He stabbed me.
Put your hands on your head now!

15:50.367 --> 15:51.869
Don't you move.

15:52.035 --> 15:55.038
Turn around and walk towards me.
Shit.

15:55.205 --> 15:56.623
<font color="#808080">ANGELA:</font>
Slowly.

15:56.790 --> 15:58.459
Go!

15:59.126 --> 16:02.754
I want everyone to wait together
by your vehicle. Biggs?

16:02.921 --> 16:05.007
<font color="#808080">BIGGS:</font>
I've got them, sheriff.

16:08.719 --> 16:09.887
Don't you move.

16:11.388 --> 16:12.556
Face down on the ground.

16:18.020 --> 16:19.313
Right hand behind your back.

16:20.898 --> 16:22.399
Left hand.

16:24.902 --> 16:25.944
<font color="#D900D9">(HANDCUFFS CLICKING)</font>

16:26.111 --> 16:27.529
Turn around.

16:40.834 --> 16:43.086
I need a wagon.
Route 96, mile marker 30.

16:43.253 --> 16:46.089
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Copy that. On <i>its</i> way.
Great, thanks.

16:48.634 --> 16:50.636
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)</font>

17:00.103 --> 17:01.939
<font color="#808080">BIGGS:</font>
Hey, sheriff.

17:03.649 --> 17:06.108
It looks like we've got
an entire pharmacy here.

17:06.276 --> 17:08.862
And the festival hasn't even started yet.

17:09.029 --> 17:11.281
It's gonna be a long night.

17:11.781 --> 17:14.701
Junior, can you stay with the car
until the tow truck arrives?

17:14.867 --> 17:17.454
Until we get a search?
I don't wanna mess up evidence.

17:17.621 --> 17:18.914
Sure thing, boss.

17:19.080 --> 17:21.083
<font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE STARTS)</font>

17:26.588 --> 17:28.590
<font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE STARTS)</font>

17:29.591 --> 17:31.593
<font color="#D900D9">(CACKLING)</font>

17:43.814 --> 17:45.315
<font color="#D900D9">(CACKLING CONTINUES)</font>

17:45.482 --> 17:47.526
What the fuck?

17:49.152 --> 17:50.571
Hey.

17:51.738 --> 17:52.990
Hold it right there.

17:54.157 --> 17:55.325
Shit!

17:55.617 --> 17:56.660
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

18:00.622 --> 18:02.457
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLING)</font>

18:02.833 --> 18:05.002
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

18:06.670 --> 18:08.463
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING AND GROANING)</font>

18:27.608 --> 18:29.109
<font color="#D900D9">(CACKLING)</font>

18:31.361 --> 18:33.363
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

18:38.994 --> 18:41.872
<font color="#D900D9">(ROCK MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS)</font>

18:42.623 --> 18:44.708
<font color="#D900D9">(PERSON BLOWING WHISTLE)</font>

18:44.875 --> 18:46.251
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font>
Hey.

18:46.418 --> 18:48.378
<font color="#D900D9">(PERSON WHISTLING)</font>

18:50.714 --> 18:52.549
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font>
That should do it.

18:53.133 --> 18:56.303
You need to have those stitches
removed in about three weeks.

18:56.470 --> 18:57.929
Thank you.

18:59.931 --> 19:02.267
All done here, sheriff.

19:21.578 --> 19:24.915
Thanks for coming, Rick.
That's all right.

19:25.082 --> 19:28.168
I know how busy it's gonna get
for you tonight.

19:28.335 --> 19:29.878
Goodbye.
Good night.

19:34.800 --> 19:36.927
You know, I just don't know
what I'm gonna do.

19:37.094 --> 19:40.097
If I get charged, they're gonna take
my scholarship away from me.

19:40.263 --> 19:43.266
We can get kicked out of school.<font color="#808080">
LITA:</font> Billy, you gotta tell her.

19:43.433 --> 19:46.478
It was your drugs, not ours.
No, no. If he claims it's all his...

19:46.645 --> 19:49.564
...they could throw the book at him.
I don't care.

19:49.731 --> 19:51.525
I'm sitting in jail because of him.

19:51.942 --> 19:58.240
I just don't know what I'm gonna do.
All right, hey, don't worry, all right?

19:59.825 --> 20:01.743
I got this.

20:02.577 --> 20:05.205
Sheriff, can I speak with you a moment?

20:05.372 --> 20:06.456
What is it?

20:06.623 --> 20:09.626
The drugs are mine.
My friends had nothing to do with it.

